    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\n![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/0f3b3c15-8ad1-4ca8-a5d9-1fe481c2ed92)\n\nwith \n```lua\nvim.diagnostic.config({\n  virtual_lines = { current_line = true },\n})\n```\nDue to the ordering of the auto command being destroyed on `hide` the diagnostic only updates for the most recently edited buffer and doesn't track the cursor correctly.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\ncreate two errors in file\ncreate split\ncreate two errors in second file\nswitch between the two splits (using `<c-w>` or `mouse` and observe that the diagnostic only redraws for the most recently edited buffer\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nerror to follow cursor\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nHEAD\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nLinux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nKitty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from source",
